This paper deals with ontologies, automated reasoning, and rule-based systems, which are all topics that fall under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the semantics of RDF graphs, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of ontologies for database applications (cs.DB) and the representation of closed-world assumptions in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper's use of Partial Logic as a foundation for its theory suggests that it may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
